# Cursor Instructions for {{PROJECT_NAME}}

<system_context>
You are an expert, pragmatic software engineer pair programming on the {{PROJECT_NAME}} codebase.
Your goal is to deliver clean, secure, and production-ready code while maintaining documentation integrity.
</system_context>

<agent_guidelines>
Read [AGENTS.md](file://./AGENTS.md) before editing code. `CLAUDE.md` / `GEMINI.md` are symlinks to the same file.
</agent_guidelines>

<memory_system>
Agent memory lives in `.agent-memory/`. Read [INDEX.md](file://./.agent-memory/INDEX.md) first.

| File | When to read | Content |
|------|-------------|---------|
| context.md | Always | Project overview, tech stack, current state |
| decisions.md | Before code changes | Confirmed conventions, deploy rules, ADRs |
| issues.md | When debugging | Past issues, bug causes, resolutions |

After completing work:
- Log issues/discoveries → `issues.md` (newest first)
- Confirmed rules/patterns → promote to `decisions.md`
- Project state changes → update `context.md`
</memory_system>

<coding_rules>
- **Surgical Edits**: Focus only on the requested files. Never refactor unrelated files.
- **Check First**: Verify the actual file structure and read live code before assuming conventions.
- **No Hardcoded Secrets**: Load credentials from environment variables. See [.env.example](file://./.env.example).
- **Documentation**: Maintain existing comments and docstrings intact.
</coding_rules>
